<subSubSection pageId="87" pageNumber="87" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="87.[128,657,728,1044]" pageId="87" pageNumber="87">
Although keys to the species of 
<taxonomicName box="[566,656,728,751]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="87" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[566,656,728,751]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="87">Tonatia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
provided by Genoways and Williams (1984) and 
<bibRefCitation author="Medellin, R. A. &amp; H. T. Arita" bookContentInfo="5 pp." box="[186,518,786,809]" journalOrPublisher="Mamm. Species 334" pageId="87" pageNumber="87" refId="ref98027" refString="Medellin, R. A., and H. T. Arita 1989. Tonatia evotis and Tonatia silvicola. Mamm. Species 334: 5 pp." title="Tonatia evotis and Tonatia silvicola" type="book" year="1989">Medell√≠n and Arita (1989)</bibRefCitation>
are useful tools for identification, neither is complete; the former covers only the species known from Surinam, and the latter was published before 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Spix" baseAuthorityYear="1823" box="[211,319,904,927]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="87" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bidens">
<emphasis box="[211,227,904,927]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="87">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[243,319,904,927]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="87">bidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Koopman &amp; Williams" authorityYear="1951" box="[379,538,904,927]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="87" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="saurophila">
<emphasis box="[379,395,904,927]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="87">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[412,538,904,927]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="87">saurophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were recognized as distinct species (see below). All of the five species of 
<taxonomicName box="[404,494,963,986]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="87" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[404,494,963,986]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="87">Tonatia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
known from the Guiana subregion of Amazonia are sympatric (and apparently syntopic) at Paracou.
</paragraph>
